Model: GPT-4 4ndr0666@gmail.com what is the nmap command to scan a local ip for the device name, os , mac basically all the data of the connected device? Nmap is a versatile tool, but no single command can fetch all the information you're looking for. However, you can combine multiple options to gather as much information as possible. Here's a command that will help you gather a device's name, OS, and MAC address, along with some additional data: bash Copy code nmap -sS -p- -O -sV -v --script=banner --system-dns -T4 Here's a breakdown of the flags used: -sS: SYN scan, a stealthy scan method.
